p can be de-normalized back to physical Compton-y units for the cluster detection and mass bias analysis.\n\n5. **Validation:**\n   - Add a specific check for the "transfer function" $T(\\ell)$ as mentioned in the dataset description. Since the MWF is a linear filter, the transfer function is analytically predictable. Comparing your empirical $T(\\ell)$ to the theoretical expectation is a critical validation step for the MWF implementation.\n\nThe plan is otherwise excellent and ready for implementation.' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='f3f5ec76-7822-4782-9936-7007f8604ac2'



