nt for *all* cross-terms, as the plan currently only mentions this for the general estimator.\n\n5. **Handling the CIB (Step 3):**\n   - Since CIB is highly non-Gaussian, the MWF (which assumes Gaussianity) might be sub-optimal. Consider adding a brief validation step to compare the MWF performance against a simple "Internal Linear Combination" (ILC) method to establish a baseline for how much the CIB-correlated noise model improves upon standard ILC.\n\nThese additions will help bridge the gap between the theoretical MWF formulation and the practical constraints of the FLAMINGO dataset.' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='0b30b465-b3ed-4dc9-a7af-8eb7ac090ef1'



